		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">DevEd wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Bump.<br /><br />Decided to do a Shantae mockup:<br /><img src="http://i.snag.gy/ayG27.jpg" alt="Image" /><br />BTW This is intended for MMC5.</div><br />This scene by itself (minus the transparent HUD, I'm sorry, I don't know any way to make that work) looks like it would easily fit within &quot;vanilla&quot; NES limitations, including attribute regions and tile count. The mossy bricks would need to be sprites though, which is perfectly fine, Marble Madness uses sprites to compensate for attribute artifacts.<br /><br />Also, don't mind all the purists, use MMC5 if you want, it's not cheating and it has everything you'd want in a mapper, plus the graphical enhancements. At this point, the only reason for using a &quot;lesser&quot; mapper (or no mapper) is if you want the challenge.

		

